2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
2 unit(s) Green Onion
9 g Sesame Seeds
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
4 tbsp Soy Sauce
4 tbsp Hoisin Sauce
113 g Sugar Snap Peas
1 tsp Sugar*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add noodles to the boiling water.
Cook uncovered until tender, 1-2 min.
Drain noodles, reserving 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) noodle water, then rinse under warm water. Return noodles to the same pot, off heat.

Thinly slice green onions.
Halve sugar snap peas crosswise.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties, garlic puree, sesame seeds, half the green onions and 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Transfer Beyond Meat® to a medium bowl. Set aside.

Reheat the same pan over medium heat.
When hot, add sugar snap peas. Cook stirring often until tender crisp, 4-5 min.

Add Beyond Meat®, sugar snap peas, soy sauce, hoisin sauce and reserved noodle water to the large pot with the noodles. Stir to combine.
Divide scallion Beyond Meat® noodles between bowls.
Sprinkle remaining green onions over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the turkey, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**